msgid "Overview"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrator-guide/dispatcher-howto.rst:7
msgid ""
"The canopsis dispatcher (or Y) allows to broadcast rabbitmq input event to "
"many targets. It is a combination of rabbitmq used as an event buffer with a"
" python script that fetch events from input queue and then post them to "
"every valid target. A valid target is defined in a configuration file and "
"broadcast works when target connection is established. A failover system "
"make failure recover possible."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrator-guide/dispatcher-howto.rst:10
msgid "How to install ?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrator-guide/dispatcher-howto.rst:12
msgid ""
"Get dispatcher zip or tar file and extract archive or github checkout from "
"canopsis_hac repository."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrator-guide/dispatcher-howto.rst:14
msgid ""
"Install command will start dispatch process, you may setup now configuration"
" file to complete install in one step (see below). Run command ``sudo "
"./install.sh`` within dispatcher directory. This will create a dispatcher "
"user and install the dispatcher system to ``/opt/dispatcher``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrator-guide/dispatcher-howto.rst:16
msgid ""
"3. Edit /opt/dispatcher/etc/targets.json . This is a json file that "
"describes where event will be routed once dispatcher daemon is started. This"
" file contains a 'target' key witch is a list of canopsis's rabbitmq "
"connection information. You must specify at least the dns name of target "
"host. optional fields are : ``port, user and vhost``."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrator-guide/dispatcher-howto.rst:42
msgid ""
"In configuration file, another field allow you to customize dispatcher "
"behavior. In **'param'** field, it is possible to set "
"**'max_failover_duration'** value in order to tell dispatcher max time that "
"dispatcher waits when a target is not reachable before trying again to "
"resume event dispatch."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrator-guide/dispatcher-howto.rst:46
msgid "How to manage ?"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrator-guide/dispatcher-howto.rst:48
msgid ""
"Once dispatcher setup, log as dispatcher user with ``sudo su - dispatcher`` "
"command. It is possible to stop both rabbitmq and dispatcher thanks to the "
"command:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrator-guide/dispatcher-howto.rst:49
msgid "``./configure start|stop``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrator-guide/dispatcher-howto.rst:51
msgid ""
"Is is also possible to only manage dispatcher activity letting rabbitmq act "
"as an event buffer while dispatcher is out of service. This is useful when "
"configuration file changes. Updating the ``targets.json`` configuration file"
" should be done with following steps:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrator-guide/dispatcher-howto.rst:52
msgid "``./service stop``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrator-guide/dispatcher-howto.rst:54
msgid ""
"Then it is possible to edit the configuration file and restart the "
"dispatcher as below."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrator-guide/dispatcher-howto.rst:55
msgid "``./service start``"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrator-guide/dispatcher-howto.rst:57
msgid "Ensure the service started by having a look at the log file:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrator-guide/dispatcher-howto.rst:58
msgid ""
"``tail -F var/log/dispatcher.log`` Soon should appear lines saying **amqp "
"Ready** and that events are sent to each target."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrator-guide/dispatcher-howto.rst:61
msgid ""
"If last message is :  **Error while parsing configuration file for "
"dispatcher targets**, then you may have a typo error in your json "
"configuration file or malformed configuration information."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrator-guide/dispatcher-howto.rst:65
msgid "Behaviors"
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrator-guide/dispatcher-howto.rst:67
msgid ""
"Log file is located in ``/opt/dispatcher/var/log/dispatcher.log`` and shows "
"sent event count every 1000 event by target."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrator-guide/dispatcher-howto.rst:69
msgid ""
"When dispatcher is ready, it starts fetching events from it's local rabbitmq"
" instance. Events are routed to python threads, one by target. events are "
"then stacked in memory until they can be sent."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrator-guide/dispatcher-howto.rst:71
msgid ""
"Sometimes when canopsis rabbitmq instance on target host restarts for "
"maintenance, the dispatcher loose connection to remote and starts waiting "
"more and more time until the max_failover_duration seconds defined in the "
"parameter file. When this limit is reached, the dispatcher tries to connect "
"again to send in memory waiting events."
msgstr ""

#: ../../administrator-guide/dispatcher-howto.rst:73
msgid ""
"If max_failover_duration is reached, in mempry events are dumped into a "
"temporary file into ``/tmp`` with ``target-name_timestamp.json`` name. Every"
" minutes, the dispatcher search for such files and if connection is restored"
" for target, events are loaded from dump files and then sent, dump files are"
" removed when they are restored."
msgstr ""

